      "Ok that is the easier case luckily :-)\r\n\r\nYou can try the following:\r\n\r\n1. Create a multi index on the right table:\r\n  ```js\r\nr.db('other_db').table('right_table').indexCreate(\"fk_multi\", r.row('fk'), {multi: true})\r\n```\r\n2. Use the following query:\r\n  ```js\r\nr.db('my_db').table('left_table')\r\n.filter(function (left) {\r\nreturn r.db('other_db').table('right_table')\r\n.getAll(left('pk'), {index: \"fk_multi\"}).isEmpty()\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis should be pretty efficient. Let me know if it works.\r\n\r\n(I'm going to close the issue because it's not a bug, but feel free to add more comments if the solution doesn't work)"
